javaspec generated an enum skeleton and proxy stubs, but --generate inserted a valueOf(String) stub that conflicts with the built-in enum method, causing a compile error. The skeleton and SpecSupport proxy methods are correct; only the valueOf stub must be removed before compilation.

Created src/main/java/com/magrathea/trustengine/domain/kms/Algorithm.java with the complete implementation (discarding the javaspec-generated skeleton's valueOf stub), then ran `../bin/javaspec run --generate` again to regenerate AlgorithmSpecSupport.java with proxy methods for curveName() and keySize(), then removed the re-inserted valueOf stub from the updated skeleton.

Algorithm.java:
  package com.magrathea.trustengine.domain.kms;

  public enum Algorithm {
      EC_P256("secp256r1", 256);

      private final String curveName;
      private final int keySize;

      Algorithm(String curveName, int keySize) {
          this.curveName = curveName;
          this.keySize = keySize;
      }

      public String curveName() {
          return curveName;
      }

      public int keySize() {
          return keySize;
      }
  }

